						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the image of Āñjanēya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1274, Yuva, Māgha, ba. 10.</hi> The Śaka year and the cyclic year do not tally.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to record some gift (details lost) made to god Tiruveṁgaḷanāthasvāmi, and to his consort, Alamēlumaṅgatāyi and also to the god Hanumān by Yannapūsa Bayyana and others.</p>						

						</summary>
